-- South Africa Richards Bay Coal Declines to Lowest in Three Weeks
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2013-01-07T13:44:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-07/south-africa-richards-bay-coal-declines-to-lowest-in-three-weeks.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, declined to their lowest level in three weeks.  Coal for  immediate delivery  dropped $1.15, or 1.3 percent,
in the week to Jan. 4 to $88.94 a metric ton, the lowest price
since Dec. 14, according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg.  The fuel is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes
delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  